data.title: News from California, across the nation and world
data.meta_description: The L.A. Times is a leading source of breaking news, entertainment, sports, politics, and more for Southern California and the world.
data.text:
Several people provided Matthew Perry with ketamine, including his live-in personal assistant who gave him injections on the day of his death, prosecutors say.

Some entertainment companies are commissioning more shows again, but the comeback remains incredibly slow. When will Hollywood workers struggling to find work get some relief?

An art exhibit at USC’s campus on Catalina Island uses artificial intelligence to propose bold ideas.

Federal authorities charged Lisa Jeanine Findley of Missouri with mail fraud and aggravated identity theft in connection with the scheme to auction off Elvis Presley’s Graceland mansion.

The corrupt IOC is taking a stand against sportsmanship, integrity and the Olympic spirit if it continues to demand Jordan Chiles return her medal.

The Supreme Court refuses to put Biden administration’s transgender school rules into effect nationwide.
